Peru Stocks: Aceros Arequipa, Cementos Lima, Minsur, Pomalca

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-06-28T22:32:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/peru-stocks-aceros-arequipa-cementos-lima-minsur-pomalca.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for a seventh session,
declining 0.7 percent to 18,719.46. The MSCI All Peru Capped
Index rose 0.1 percent to 2,434.37.  Industrial and mining stocks slumped because of investor
uncertainty over the policies of President-elect Ollanta Humala,
said Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru. Humala
takes office July 28.  Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based
steelmaker, fell 5.2 percent to 2.35 soles. Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a unit of Grupo Oviedo,
dropped 4.1 percent to 47 centimos.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest
cement maker, slid 2.6 percent to 2.29 soles. Luz del Sur
(LUSURC1 PE), Peru’s largest electricity distributor, dropped
2.5 percent to 6.24 soles.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, fell 4.6 percent to 3.12 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  